==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pendentive
<hw>Pen*den"tive</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧n*d⟦ecr⟧nt"⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>pendentif</ets>, fr. L. <ets>pendere</ets> to hang.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The portion of a vault by means of
which the square space in the middle of a building is brought to an
octagon or circle to receive a cupola.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The part
of a groined vault which is supported by, and springs from, one pier or
corbel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pendently</ent>⟦br⟧
